{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Criminalise smoking on NHS hospital grounds",
        "additional_details": "Give police the power to arrest and charge people who have contravened the ban.\r\n \r\nSmoking near healthcare facilities poses serious health risks to patients, visitors, and healthcare workers.\r\n \r\nNHS hospitals strive to be smoke-free zones, but we believe current efforts to enforce this via signage and security patrols are ineffective.\r\n \r\nWe think making smoking on NHS hospital grounds a criminal offence is the most effective way to combat this deeply concerning issue.\r\n \r\nSmoking on hospital grounds is harmful and undermines efforts to protect public health.\r\n",
        "background": "This petition urges the UK Government to introduce legislation to ban smoking on all NHS hospital grounds across the country.",
